commit.message:
make the output-buffer larger

8192 length could make sense in 1987, but right now it is too limiting. Bumping
it 8x is not a big problem, but allows for larger strings to be rendered.

commit.message:
buffer-read-default: handle gracefully eof and partial reads

When some data is read (but not all), return a non-NIL value:

- :end-of-file when no data is read
- :truncated when some (but not all) data is read

This change in behavior was proposed and initially implemented by Alastair
Bridgewater here: https://github.com/sharplispers/clx/pull/203.
dependent: unify common code in a file "common"

xrender: ensure that the clip mask is always updated

Previously the clip-mask and the server value were compared with EQL when the
picture was synchronized, and the clip-mask was assigned to the server-value.
This approach breaks when the client (preasumbly to avoid consing) modifies
the vector directly. In that case the new value and the server value are EQ
while the clip still needs to be updated.

To avoid this problem when the clip-mask is a sequence, then we ensure that it
is a distinct vector.

Fixes #201.
